20/02/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Authorities seized documents and ammunition in separate operations directed against the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), in the southeast regions of Van and Sirnak on Monday (February 19th). 
According to press reports, police found documents related to the PKK during searches of a local office of the pro-Kurdish Democratic Society Party in Van. 
They arrested 20 people. 
Separately, Turkish security forces seized a substantial amount of arms and munitions supposedly designated for the PKK, hidden underground in Sirnak province.
Local media in Ankara reported on Tuesday that the government is discussing whether to launch contacts with Iraqi Kurdish leaders, in the context of fighting the PKK. 
Turkey maintains that the group has bases in northern Iraq. 
(Sabah, Zaman, Cumhuriyet - 20/02/07)
